  "prompt": "How do you factory reset an iPhone 4 without a computer?",
  "response": "To factory reset an iPhone 4 without a computer, you can follow these steps directly on the device:\n\n1. **Back Up Your Data (Optional):** Before you reset your iPhone, you might want to back up your important data, as a factory reset will erase everything.\n\n2. **Open Settings:** Tap the \u201cSettings\u201d app on your iPhone.\n\n3. **Go to General:** Scroll down and tap on \u201cGeneral.\u201d\n\n4. **Scroll Down:** Near the bottom of the General menu, look for \u201cReset\u201d and tap on it.\n\n5. **Choose Erase All Content and Settings:** In the Reset menu, tap on \u201cErase All Content and Settings.\u201d\n\n6. **Confirm Your Decision:** You may be prompted to enter your passcode. After that, you will see a warning message informing you that this will erase all media and data. Confirm that you want to proceed by tapping \u201cErase iPhone.\u201d\n\n7. **Wait for the Process to Complete:** The iPhone will reboot and start the reset process. This may take a few minutes.\n\n8. **Set Up Your iPhone:** After the reset is complete, your iPhone will display the setup screen as it did when it was new.\n\nRemember, this process will completely erase all data on your iPhone, so make sure to back anything you need beforehand!",
